text: <@UGK9N4JJ2>, how you feeling about the podcast idea after it's stewed for a weekend?

So I chewed on it over the weekend, and I had a thought.

Perhaps instead of pigeonholing the podcast into specifically Brawl, perhaps make it about Multiplayer Magic in general, with a focus on Brawl? That way there is flexibility to talk some EDH if you want, or even something like Oathbreaker or whatever the flavor of the month might be?

Just something I thought I should ask about since that came up in my thoughts on the topic. I’m always much more of a fan of being broad and being able to adapt as opposed to putting myself in a situation where I’m constrained. I’d like to hear your thoughts on it though.

I'm not totally opposed to it, and I think Brawlbreakers might even work as a title to it whether oathbreaker survives or just becomes a joke. I'd love to be able to joke about joust and discuss pEDH, for sure.
I’m really high on Oathbreaker right now tbh. I just made a Battle Box and all the games have been nail biters
Gosh, I played Pauper EDH. Despite the lack of quality boardwipes, it was fun
How affordable are the decks in that box, Angelo?

Concerns:

* Brawl is going to have a significant 1v1 presence with Arena.
* Is there an audience for general multiplayer variant talk?
* Will we have content when there isn't a flavor of the month?
* There's no way we can be experts in all of this, right?
Not too sure honestly. I’ll see if I can throw the lists on Archidekt tonight
I’m already thinking of adding up to four more decks, but I’m not sure

Thoughts:
* 1v1 Brawl can and should be talked about imo since it is an offshoot of a multiplayer format that people would be interested in. These kinds of corner cases is why I think flexibility is important.
* I think that C19 could be used to bring people in and then get them to stay when talking about other formats. I know a lot of casual people want to try new things. Secret partners, archenemy, emperor, I’ve played all those when starting out. 
* At worst one could deviate back to EDH or Brawl or Deck techs if there was downtime.
* I don’t think any podcast right now can break into the scene while trying to look like experts in anything anymore. There is just too much content. I think having a primary focus and talking about a few different things at first could be a good litmus test to see what kind of content works the best.

Probably shouldn't have voted on that poll, then. I think you've convinced me, though.

How do you feel about the name? Too specific, too related to genitalia, or right on?

Also, if any of the above, what are some other ideas?

At worst, if the podcast were to start off being a bit more broad, once you were to get some numbers and feedback, you can specialize it from there, especially considering going in on Brawl is a bit risky to begin with. 

I think the name is...Fine. Not great, but bad, but okay. I think it could be changed without losing anything though.

Ideas in terms of what exactly? Like topics-wise?
Alternate names. Topic wise I think we're fine right now with the release of brawl specific cards and the popularity of ob
I could talk for an hour about just the new signet as it relates to brawl and edh.
Although I think I'd like to keep episodes closer to 15-20 minutes.
You think so? What are your thoughts on the reason for the shorter length?
I feel like the typical gaming podcast has a lot of fluff. 15 minutes of intro before getting to the actual topic, etc. I'd rather be more focused and be a commute podcast.

That’s fair. I do think that a little fluff is good, that way people would have time to get to know the hosts a bit. BSB has retained listeners because of the hosts + finance advice as opposed to just finance advice alone.
I like CMDR Central’s first 10 minutes talking about games they played or a little miscellaneous segment. Maybe 20-30 minutes could be workable?
I get the idea of cutting out fluff. You can’t have a cake made of icing, but most people will want a bit of icing on the cake, y’know?
I'm down with that.
So that leaves... music, outline, and scheduling?
So I was looking at the assist cards from Battlebond for name inspirations. There are a couple that catch my eye, but I was to now what you think.

All right, first show topic: 

What EDH variant will "make it"?
I'll take the pro side for brawl, then the con side for ob, then we both unabashedly support joust.
I had an idea for an episode: How Brawl is beneficial for EDH (despite what people may say) :point_right::sunglasses::point_right:
Fuck yeah. Joust is the best
Better than EDH. It’ll get bigger too

Yeah, that's pretty much the conversation I had in mind for the new Talisman, only in reverse. But I will definitely agree that the new Legendaries mostly meant for Brawl are an absolute boon for Commander, especially since they aren't getting the terrible caveats that come with the Commander Product commanders.
But seriously, I'm super excited about this. Let me know when/if you're available, and let's put a show together.

I’m pretty busy with my two jobs, but I might be able to make some more free time per week soon. I’m usually free most nights after 9:30 (eastern), and then varying times Thursday-Friday. Sunday I’m free after 8. We should set up a Skype call and just shoot the shit and see how it goes.
